agent.text: Determining the "best" TV series in history is subjective and depends on personal preferences and opinions. However, it is worth mentioning that Saturday Night Live is one of the longest running comedy series on TV; it debuted in October 1975 and is now in its 42nd season, if longevity can be considered a criteria for 'best.'

contexts.text:
The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson
In order to work fewer days each week , Carson began to petition network executives in 1974 that reruns on the weekends be discontinued , in favor of showing them on one or more nights during the week . In response to his demands , NBC created a new comedy / variety series to feed to affiliates on Saturday nights that debuted in October 1975 , Saturday Night Live , which is now in its 42nd season .
contexts.title: The Tonight Show Starring Johnny Carson

contexts.text:
The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon
Jimmy Fallon , a former cast member on Saturday Night Live , was appointed as the third host of Late Night by executive producer Lorne Michaels in 2009 when Conan moved to Tonight . Fallon incorporated the Internet much more than other talk shows . Between Fallon 's own musical sensibilities and the recruitment of his house band , hip - hop collective The Roots , his incarnation of Late Night `` evolved into the most deeply musical of TV 's musical - comedy variety programs '' , with sketches in which he parodies Neil Young and Bruce Springsteen going viral online . Coincidentally , it was during the Tonight Show debacle that Fallon 's show found its footing . The show , according to Fallon 's former SNL castmate Tina Fey , established itself as `` an uncommonly warm , welcoming show . '' In 2010 , New York complimented Fallon 's `` good humor '' and noted his improvement : `` In the relative safety of his 12 : 35 a.m. time slot , Fallon has been cultivating a distinct , and refreshing , strain of humor : the comedy of unabashed celebration . '' `` In our heads , we 've been doing The Tonight Show ( ... ) We 're just on at a later hour , '' Fallon said .
contexts.title: The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon

contexts.text:
Rob Schneider
Schneider was hired at Saturday Night Live in 1988 . Schneider swiftly graduated from writer and featured player to full cast member . From 1990 to 1994 at SNL , he played such roles as `` Tiny Elvis '' and `` Orgasm Guy '' . His best known recurring character was Richard Laymer , an office worker whose desk was stuck beside the photocopier , and who addressed each of his fellow employees with an endless stream of annoying nicknames . Schneider is featured in the video release The Bad Boys of Saturday Night Live , along with colleagues Adam Sandler , Chris Rock , David Spade , and Chris Farley . Recurring

agent.original_text: Determining the "best" TV series in history is subjective and depends on personal preferences and opinions. The Office is often considered one of the greatest sitcoms of all time due to its unique mockumentary style, memorable characters, and relatable humor. However, there are many other critically acclaimed and popular TV series that could also be considered the "best" in history.
